# ENT-001 durable journal bucket split: .runtime/ is ignored by default, but
# the DURABLE governance evidence buckets are un-ignored (tracked) so a fresh
# clone can validate its own board: the journal and the canonical plan records.
# Locks, sessions, agents.json, gate-procs, session-threads, the latest-snapshot
# pointer, and scratch stay ignored. Use `.runtime/*` (NOT `.runtime/`) so git
# descends into the dir and the `!` negations below can re-include.
# This mirrors the root .gitignore; the deeper coord/.gitignore is consulted
# for paths under coord/, so the negation must live in BOTH files.
.runtime/*
!.runtime/governance-events.ndjson
# COORD-105: the per-mutation governance-snapshots/ history bucket is NOT
# tracked (board validate never reads it; tracking caused unbounded git bloat).
# COORD-108: governance-latest-snapshot.json is likewise NOT tracked — a single
# regenerable board-state-at-last-mutation pointer that MUTATES on every gov
# command (perpetually-dirty worktree), not needed for fresh-clone validate.
# Both kept on local disk as recovery scratch.
!.runtime/plans/
.worktrees/
.session-thread-*
agents.json
agent_sessions.json
locks/*.lock
locks/
memory/

# Gate artifacts are runtime output of `gov gate` / the repo gate.sh runners
# (coverage reports + the COORD-080 complete gate artifact JSON). Generated, not
# tracked.
artifacts/gates/

# C6-P3: root-level rendered compat mirrors are generated by
# `board.js sync` (writeCompatibilityCopy). They stay on disk for
# consumers but are no longer tracked. Anchored so the canonical
# tracked views under rendered/ are NOT ignored.
/TASKS.md
/PROMPT_INDEX.md
